Police in Migori County have launched investigations into the death of a man whose body was on Sunday morning found lying on the Migori-Isebania road at Total area. Suna East sub-county Police Commander Esau Ochorokodi said they suspect that the deceased committed suicide by consuming a poisonous chemical, adding that there was foam coming out of his mouth. Mr. Ochorokodi said their preliminary investigation established that the deceased, who hails from Oruba estate, quarrelled with and assaulted his wife on Saturday night accusing her of infidelity, before his body was discovered the following morning. He said they have since launched further probe into the matter to establish finer details of what transpired before his death. The body of the deceased was moved to the Migori referral hospital mortuary pending autopsy. Also Read: Video Of The Day: Former sports CS Hassan Wario convicted over Rio games scam